By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has confirmed 676 new cases of #COVID-19 in Nigeria. The 676 confirmed cases were recorded from 19 states with Lagos State – the epicentre of the novel virus infection leading the table with 227 cases followed by Rivers with 73 while Niger and plateau came third and fourth with 69 and 56 cases respectively. Others are: FCT-50; Kano-44; Oyo-43; Ogun-27; Gombe-18; Ondo-15; Enugu and Osun-10 each; Cross River and Edo-8 each; Nasarawa-7; Bauchi-4; Kaduna-3 whileEkiti and Zamfara recorded 2 cases each. The health agency in the report released via it’s twitter, further informed that with the new confirmed infections, the total confirmed cases have risen to 131,918 out of which 106,275 patients have been discharged From various isolation centres in Nigeria. The NCDC regrettably reported  that 1,607 lives have been lost to COVID-19 related complications since the index case was reported in February 27, 2020 in Nigeria. See the breakdown of total confirmed cases below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The latest report from the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has confirmed that the total confirmed cases of COVID-19 has risen risen to 56,388 with the 132 new infections reported on Monday night. This NCDC in report released via its twitter handle account… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The total confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria hit 59,001 as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported 153 new fresh infections on Thursday. Similarly, the NCDC report released via it's twitter handle account further said that the total of 50, 452… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The latest COVID-19 report released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has it that Lagos State, the epicentre of the novel virus, accounted for 642 infections as the health agency confirmed 1,074 new cases on Monday. According to the report rel